node.text:
The London Contemporary Orchestra performing Isobel Waller-Bridge’s Arise at the Alexander McQueen Spring/Summer 2020 show.
As part of our #McQueenCreators series we will be sharing #McQueenMusic with you.

Visit our Spotify channel to hear playlists inspired by Alexander McQueen shows and featuring their soundtracks. 
Follow the link in our bio to listen to our #McQueenMusic playlists.

The Alexander McQueen Autumn/Winter 2020 show in Paris. “The collection is a love letter to women and to families, colleagues and friends. We went to Wales and were inspired by the warmth of its artistic and poetic heritage, by its folklore and the soul of its craft. The woman is courageous, grounded, bold: heroic. There is a sense of protection in the clothes, of safety and comfort, evoked through quilting and blankets. The hearts are a symbol of togetherness, of being there for others.” Sarah Burton Creative Director 
#McQueenAW20 #PFW #AlexanderMcQueen

node.text:
Follow Head of Atelier, Judy Halil, as she gives a step-by-step demonstration and insight into the expertise of the studio at Alexander McQueen.

Here she makes one of the centrepieces of the Roses installation: the swirling red Rose dress by Sarah Burton from the Autumn/Winter 2019 collection.

Visit the installation at #27OldBondStreet, our London flagship.

Video by @MashaVasyukova.

#AlexanderMcQueen

node.text:
The swirling red Rose dress from the Autumn/Winter 2019 collection.⁣
 ⁣
The folding petal-form dynamics of the shape and the upstanding collar could only be brought to life sculpturally, in 3D.⁣
 ⁣
The silhouette was initially draped on the house model by Sarah Burton and her studio team.⁣
 ⁣
The techniques needed to capture the abundant asymmetry of a natural rose were devised with Sarah and Judy Halil, Head of the Atelier, in an intensive process of pin-tucking in the neckline and free-form gathering of whorls in the volume of the skirt.⁣
⁣
See the #McQueenRoses installation at #27OldBondStreet, our London flagship.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Photographed by @ChloeLeDrezen.
